# Bug 03: Language selector text overflow on mobile layout

## Description
In mobile view, the language selector button (e.g. "English") does not properly handle long text input. When extended text is used, characters overflow outside the button boundary.

## Steps to reproduce
1. Open site on mobile device or mobile viewport (DevTools)
2. Locate language selector near “Sign in” button
3. Replace language label with longer text (or simulate long string)
4. Observe layout behavior

## Actual result
Text overflows outside button boundaries, breaking layout consistency.

## Expected result
Text should be truncated, wrapped, or constrained within the button container.

## Environment
- Mobile viewport (Chrome DevTools)
- Android browser (tested manually)

## Severity
Medium (UI/UX issue)

